# Architecture

## Stack

- Vite, React, React Router ([package.json](@package.json)).
- **Tailwind CSS v4** via `@tailwindcss/vite` ([vite.config.js](@vite.config.js)); design tokens and `@import "tailwindcss"` live in [src/index.css](@src/index.css).

## Layout

- **Pages:** add under `src/pages/` as `*.jsx` components.
- **Routes and nav:** register in [src/routes.jsx](@src/routes.jsx) (`navRoutes`: `path`, `label`, `element`).
- **App shell:** [src/App.jsx](@src/App.jsx) renders sidebar + `<Routes>` from `navRoutes`.
- **Bootstrap:** [src/main.jsx](@src/main.jsx).

## Conventions

- Prefer functional components and **Tailwind utility classes** for layout and styling in `src/`.
- Use [src/cn.js](@src/cn.js) (`clsx` + `tailwind-merge`) when combining conditional utilities (for example active nav links or calendar day states).
- Keep new routes and labels consistent with current `navRoutes` entries.
- Do not introduce new top-level folders without a clear need; stay aligned with this small SPA structure.
- Avoid large bespoke CSS in `index.css` unless extending `@theme` or base layers; prefer utilities in components.

## UI entrypoints (playground SPA)

Concrete references for [ui-system.mdc](@.cursor/rules/ui-system.mdc) in this repo:

- **App shell and navigation:** [src/App.jsx](@src/App.jsx) — sidebar, main content area, `<Routes>` from `navRoutes` (Tailwind utilities + `NavLink` active states via `cn()`).
- **Global styles:** [src/index.css](@src/index.css) — `@import "tailwindcss"`, `@theme` color and font tokens, minimal `@layer base`.
- **Reference pages:** [src/pages/Home.jsx](@src/pages/Home.jsx), [src/pages/Info.jsx](@src/pages/Info.jsx) — max-width content column, lead paragraph, and section/list patterns expressed as utilities.

## Cross-cutting policy

- Git and PR rules: [git-workflow.mdc](@.cursor/rules/git-workflow.mdc).
- UI consistency: [ui-system.mdc](@.cursor/rules/ui-system.mdc).
